  "source": "2019 RIRR of RA 9514",
  "last_verified": "2026-06-27",
  "notes": "Occupant Load Factor (OLF) = floor area per person.\nTo calculate occupant load: Total Floor Area / OLF = Number of Occupants.\nUse the most restrictive (smallest) OLF when multiple uses apply.\n",
